well...it's over. after 3 years of sweet sweet loving, Rupert the fish has moved to a new home in the Toronto Sewer System. this has strangely happened, maddy, about 4 days after the death of your fishy friend. it was so sad. he was at the bottom of his tank, all white coloured and hardened. i cried alot. i'm a suck like that. but that didn't stop me from going to the pet store an hour later. is that bad? i'm not "replacing" him. rupert was the best fish ever. he was pretty and swimmy and strong and i lost 5 points for having him in rez. he was my fishy lover. but we went to fairview (me dad and parnian aka the dognapper) anddddd we were looking at the fishes, and i picked this pretty swimmy red one..but then i was thinking...you will not be able to see him in the tank that i have because they are the same colour. so i picked a green tank with neon rocks. then my daddy said "why dont you get another fish to put in the old tank?" and i gladly accepted this suggestion. so along with the red beta that i got, also got a crown beta (crazy feathered fishy)to put in rupert's old tank. so. after much debating of names (jacques, frankenstein) and then more names to do with psych and history (freud, adler, satir, goebbles, himmler), i settled on Hans and Sophie, even though they are both boy fishes. hans and sophie scholl were a brother and sister duo during WWII who got together with some other people and formed a youth resistance group called The White Rose, and together they created and handed out anti-nazi leaflets. after the 5th one, they got caught and subsequently arrested and killed under hitler's rule. i wrote an esay this year that had a lot to do with them, and also saw the Sophie Scholl movie at bayview village in april (which was amazing even though it was german, maddy lets watch it again). so..there you have it, the history nerd in me has come out. and rupert is no more. only in my heart.

well...i fell into the fad...and sadly, i have purchased an ipod. now...i'm not quite sure how this happened. i was just looking on craigslist.com...and there you can get used stuff for super cheap. so i got a black 2GB ipod slightly used for 150. i saved 100 dollars....not that i should have been spending my money on this in the first place. i'm actually pretty dissapointed in myself. for some reason i've always hated apple. i think its because of grade 3. remember how the teachers used to make all the kids spend time on the computers during class? and you'd get stickers everytime you did it? well i dreaded those days...i was technologically impaired and i cried when it was my turn. now in grade 3 we had 2 MACS and 2 APPLES. the apple computers were the math computers where all you could do was play stupid math games in the lonely stinky hallway of the school. i think i was traumatized by my inability to turn on the computer and...even once that was done, to get any questions right on the freaking games. yeah im pretty sure thats where my hate comes from. so when ipods came out, i made fun of everyone who spent their money on them...500 songs..who would need 500 songs on their freaking thing. im sorry to say that i only made it half way though my music library before my ipods memory was full and i had to purge some of my sweet sweet britney spears and abba music. so im sitting here...listening to it..and its good...and i like the clicking noise that it makes when i touch the wheel...and i just bought 3 ipod skins off ebay for a grand total of 8.47 which i must say is pretty good. shipping can be retardedly expensive. but anyways...i still am a little pissed that i had to be so freaking uncreative. i mean, its pretty...and its works...but i don't like apple. damn you, you stupid round fruit.
